Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+):

## 1. Windows-only tests — `[OSCondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Setting", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI — `[CICondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void RenderFrame_UsesLocalGpu()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.RenderTestFrame();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 3. Flaky external API — `[Retry]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task GetWeather_ReturnsData(TestContext testContext)
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions.

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — `[TestCleanup]` or `IDisposable`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class TempFileTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public TempFileTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void WriteThenRead_RoundTrips()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "hello");
        Assert.AreEqual("hello", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    // Runs even if the test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

Alternatively, use `[TestCleanup]` which also runs on failure:

```csharp
[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}
```

**Execution order guarantee:** `[TestCleanup]` → `IAsyncDisposable` → `IDisposable` — all run regardless of test outcome.

---

**Summary of attributes:**

| Scenario | Attribute | MSTest version |
|----------|-----------|----------------|
| OS-specific | `[OSCondition(...)]` | 3.10+ |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` | 3.10+ |
| Retry flaky | `[Retry(N)]` | 3.9+ |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `IDisposable` or `[TestCleanup]` | All |
